Incident.Summary: The juvenile defendant physically assaulted her intimate partner, and then made statements about self harm.

VICTIM/COMPLAINANT:

Tony Douglas Venable Jr, 10/2/2003


WITNESS/NEIGHBORHOOD CHECK:

Leah Jacobs, 6/17/2000

Jacobs provided a written statement regarding her observations. Jacobs advised that she heard Tony and Mackenzie arguing upstairs, so she came up to see what was going on. Jacobs explained that she heard Mackenzie yelling and screaming at Tony as he had attempted to lock himself in the bathroom. Jacobs observed Mackenzie with a bread knife as she was yelling and threatening Tony. Jacobs indicated that she had then called 911 after trying to calm Mackenzie down.


SUSPECT/DEFENDANT:

Mackenzie Elizabeth Grossnickle, 4/12/2005


SCENE PROCESSING:

-Myself, Cpl Mattingly, and TFC Coss collected Body Worn Camera footage.
-TFC Coss completed the Lethality Screen and Domestic Violence Supplement with Venable. 
-TFC Coss took two (2) digital photographs of Venable's injuries.
-TFC Coss acquired a written statement from Venable.


NARRATIVE:

On 3/10/2023 at approximately 1321 hours, I, S/Tpr Hopkins #6060, of the Maryland State Police, Frederick Barrack, was on duty in full uniform.

I was dispatched to respond to 11363 Wolfsville Road, Myersville, MD for the report of a domestic in progress. Dispatch advised that the female had a kitchen knife during the incident. Myself, Cpl Mattingly and TFC Coss responded to the area which was later determined to be 11363 Highland School Road, Myersville, MD. Upon arrival, Cpl Mattingly and I contacted the female party, identified as Mackenzie Elizabeth Grossnickle, 4/12/2005, who had answered the door and allowed us to enter. We asked what was going on, to which she stated that she and her boyfriend had an argument. Grossnickle further explained that they have heated arguments from time to time, and that they get loud. The male party, identified as Tony Douglas Venable Jr., 10/2/2003, came downstairs wearing a hoodie and appeared disheveled. Venable confirmed the loud argument they were having, and indicated that he had some small scratches on his body. When asked if the fight escalated and became physical, he denied it being physical. Grossnickle stated that the argument stemmed from her suspicion that Venable had been talking to his ex-girlfriend, and when she confronted him it escalated. I separated the parties when TFC Coss arrived a short while later, and Cpl Mattingly responded to the basement area of the residence to contact the complainants/witnesses.

I spoke with Venable outside to get a better story separate from Grossnickle. I further inquired about the incident, asking if it became physical, to which he claimed "Not really". I noted that he had small scratch marks on his face, and then observed a large scratch on the right side of his neck. He pulled his hood out of the way and revealed fairly large scratch marks consistent with fingernail markings. Venable seemed to try to downplay the injuries and indicated that he didn't want Grossnickle to get in trouble and that he didn't want anything done. Cpl Mattingly had stepped outside at which point we learned of further injuries to Venable's person. Venable stated he had some scratches on his back, which he then pulled up the back of his sweatshirt revealing very large and deep scratch marks consistent with fingernail markings. Venable was asked how long he and Grossnickle were dating, to which he indicated about ten (10) months. Venable also indicated that he had been living with her at that residence for the same amount of time. Venable further indicated that their relationship had been sexual in nature. At this time, I determined Grossnickle to be the aggressor and caused physical injury to Venable during a domestic argument.

Grossnickle was placed in handcuffs by Cpl Mattingly, at which time she became irate. Grossnickle then said "TJ, I hate you, I fucking hate you" towards Venable. She then said "Bro I'm killing myself" and "take me to the psych ward, I'm not going to jail". At this time, I believed her to be a danger to herself and others, as evidenced by her attack on Venable, and she would be emergency petitioned. I took custody of Grossnickle and placed her in my patrol vehicle in accordance with MSP policies and procedures. I transported Grossnickle to Frederick Health Hospital at 400 W. 7th Street, Frederick, MD for the emergency evaluation. While waiting in the triage area with Grossnickle commented about her nails being broken. I looked at her nails and observed several of them to be short and broken off. I completed the EP District Court form and released Grossnickle to the care of FHH staff. The parents of Grossnickle were contacted and advised of the incident. Jonathan Jay Grossnickle, Mackenzie's biological father, had been contacted and was initially unhelpful. Amy Jo Tessier, Mackenzie's biological mother was contacted and advised that she had taken custody of Mackenzie upon release from FHH. Tessier advised she would respond to the Frederick Barrack to sign the juvenile release. Tessier indicated that she has shared custody of Mackenzie, and that she does not agree with the way Jonathan Grossnickle allows her to remain at that residence unsupervised. Tessier further indicated that she has civil process pending against Jonathan Grossnickle for violating the custody agreement. I completed an MSP 53, Juvenile Release for Tessier to sign when she responds to the barrack.

All above events occurred in Frederick County, Maryland.


CHARGES:

3-203 Second Degree Assault (Juvenile Referral)


CASE STATUS:

Closed on Arrest (Referral)

NARRATIVE:

On March 13, 2023, at approximately 1157 hours, I attempted to contact Venable, Tony Douglas DOB: 10-02-2003 in reference to a Domestic Violence Follow-up where he was listed as the victim of domestic assault. On the MSP 246 I observed there was no telephone number listed. I check for a telephone number on his RMS profile, which revealed a telephone number; 301-663-5849. I attempted to call the telephone number and was promptly forwarded to voicemail. The voicemail had a greeting for a George Smallwood subject. I attempted to contact Venable via an email listed on his RMS profile; tjvenables@gmail.com. 

CASE STATUS: Pending additional follow-up.

NARRATIVE:

On March 30, 2023 at approximately 0912 hours, I, TFC J. Reever #5910, attempted to contact Venable again via the telephone number listed in RMS. The telephone rang several times before I was forwarded to voicemail again. As of this date, all attempts to contact Venable have been negative. 

CASE STATUS: This concludes my portion of the investigation.
